name: Big Daddy Quin
description: Hello, fellow members of IEEE. I pose the following question for you. Why do we harbour this emotion called struggle in school? Why do we subject ourselves to the supposed torment of lost time that is a bachelor's degree? Why do we then indulge ourselves in destructive behaviour in an effort to mitigate the onslaught of our responsibilities? Is it a feeling of duty, that is sometimes overshadowed by an exploration of the unknown? Boredom is the trigger for lust. Curiosity and its subsequent satisfaction is the mistress to our alleged journey to greatness. But is it worth it all?
